Israeli Stocks: Allot Communications, D. Medical, Nova Measuring

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-08-02T10:42:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/israeli-stocks-allot-communications-d-medical-nova-measuring.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index fell for a fifth
day, declining 0.5 percent to 1,1193.83 at 12:50 p.m. in Tel
Aviv.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Allot Communications Ltd. (ALLT)   retreated 2.2 percent
to 50.89 shekels, the lowest level since June 15. Israel’s
biggest maker of high-speed networking equipment plans to issue
4.5 million shares and shareholders will offer 965,000 shares.  D. Medical Industries Ltd. (DMED IT) climbed the most
since May 3, increasing 9.5 percent to 12.47 shekels. The
Israeli maker of drug-delivery devices signed the first U.S.
distribution agreement for its Spring Universal Infusion sets.  Nova Measuring Instruments Ltd. (NVMI)   slumped to the
lowest since Dec. 21, dropping 3.8 percent to 29.08 shekels. The
maker of measuring instruments for the semiconductor industry
forecast third-quarter revenue of $24 million to $27 million
with net profitability of 20 percent to 25 percent. Revenue was
$29.6 million in the second-quarter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in  Tel Aviv  at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
